20reserves%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20for%20suitable%20locations%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyanrenewables.com%2Focean-infinity-and-cyan-renewables-form-technology-partnership-to-advance-offshore-wind-projects-in-the-asia-pacific-region%5C%22%3Eoffshore%20renewable%20energy%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20has%20also%20proved%20it%20is%20capable%20of%20locating%20underwater%20wreckage%20in%20the%20past.%20For%20example%2C%20in%202018%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deepoceansearch.com%2F2018%2F11%2F19%2Focean-infinity-announce-finding-ara-san-juan%2F%5C%22%3Efound%20a%20missing%20Argentinian%20navy%20submarine%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%201%2C000%20metres%20underwater%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean.%20And%20last%20October%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmart-news%2Fthis-newly-discovered-sunken-warship-served-on-both-sides-of-world-war-ii-180985192%2F%5C%22%3Eit%20found%20the%20wreck%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20US%20Navy%20ship%20that%20had%20been%20underwater%20for%2078%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20search%20area%20for%20MH370%20is%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20metropolitan%20Sydney.%20It%20was%20identified%20in%20collaboration%20with%20experts%20based%20on%20refined%20analysis%20of%20information%20received%20after%20the%20aircraft%20disappeared.%20This%20information%20included%20weather%2C%20satellite%20data%20and%20the%20location%20of%20debris%20attributed%20to%20the%20aircraft%20which%20washed%20up%20along%20the%20coast%20of%20Africa%20and%20islands%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20search%2C%20Ocean%20Infinity%20will%20be%20using%20a%20new%2078%20metre%20offshore%20support%20vessel%2C%20the%20Armada%207806.%20It%20was%20built%20by%20Norwegian%20shipbuilder%20Vard%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EAdvanced%20sonar%20technology%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Armada%207806%20is%20equipped%20with%20a%20fleet%20of%20autonomous%20underwater%20vehicles%20manufactured%20by%20the%20Norwegian%20firm%20Kongsberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%206.2m%20long%20vehicles%20are%20capable%20of%20operating%20independently%20of%20the%20support%20vessel%20at%20depths%20of%20up%20to%206%2C000m%20for%20up%20to%20100%20hours%20at%20a%20time.%20They%20are%20equipped%20with%20advanced%20sonar%20technology%2C%20including%20sidescan%2C%20synthetic%20aperture%2C%20multibeam%20and%20sub-bottom%20profiling%20sonar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESonar%20systems%20are%20essential%20for%20underwater%20mapping%20and%20object%20detection%20surveys.%20They%20use%20acoustic%20pulses%20to%20look%20for%20echoes%20from%20the%20seafloor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESidescan%20sonar%20captures%20high-resolution%20images%20of%20the%20seafloor%20by%20sending%20out%20pulses%20of%20sound%20and%20detecting%20objects%20that%20reflect%20the%20sound%20pulses%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESynthetic%20aperture%20sonar%20is%20a%20technique%20for%20combining%20the%20results%20from%20multiple%20%26quot%3Bpings%26quot%3B%20to%20effectively%20make%20the%20scanner%20bigger%20and%20more%20powerful%2C%20seeing%20further%2C%20and%20producing%20more%20detailed%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultibeam%20sonar%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20maps%20the%20seafloor%20topography%20by%20emitting%20multiple%20sonar%20beams%20in%20a%20fan-shaped%20pattern%20below%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20sub-bottom%20profiling%20sonar%20operates%20at%20lower%20frequencies%20and%20penetrates%20the%20seabed%20to%20reveal%20underlying%20geological%20structures.%20This%20is%20useful%20for%20archaeological%20studies%2C%20sediment%20analysis%20and%20identifying%20buried%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%2C%20these%20sonar%20technologies%20provide%20complementary%20data%20for%20underwater%20exploration%2C%20search%20and%20recovery%2C%20and%20geological%20assessments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECamera%20systems%20and%20lights%20on%20the%20vehicles%20may%20be%20used%20to%20confirm%20potential%20targets.%20Once%20a%20target%20of%20interest%20is%20detected%20using%20sonar%2C%20the%20vehicles%20would%20be%20programmed%20with%20missions%20designed%20to%20operate%20significantly%20closer%20to%20the%20seafloor.%20This%20would%20allow%20them%20to%20capture%20imagery%20of%20the%20search%20area%20with%20which%20to%20identify%20the%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20search%20would%20only%20be%20conducted%20once%20a%20target%20of%20interest%20is%20identified%2C%20as%20the%20area%20covered%20by%20each%20image%20is%20significantly%20smaller%20than%20that%20covered%20by%20sonar%2C%20therefore%20requiring%20much%20denser%20survey%20tracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESignificant%20advancements%20in%20robotics%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20previous%20search%20in%202018%2C%20Ocean%20Infinity%20has%20made%20significant%20advancements%20in%20its%20marine%20robotics%20and%20data%20analytics%20capabilities.%20It%20has%20demonstrated%20its%20capacity%20to%20simultaneously%20deploy%20multiple%20vehicles%20at%20depths%20of%20up%20to%206%2C000m.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20significantly%20increases%20the%20coverage%20area%2C%20as%20each%20vehicle%20covers%20its%20own%20patch%20of%20seafloor.%20This%20will%20allow%20for%20a%20more%20efficient%20and%20comprehensive%20survey%20of%20the%20designated%20search%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20being%20collected%20by%20the%20vehicles%20will%20be%20downloaded%20once%20the%20vehicles%20are%20brought%20back%20onboard%2C%20and%20stitched%20together%20to%20provide%20detailed%20maps%20of%20the%20search%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EDifficult%20conditions%2C%20above%20and%20below%20the%20surface%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConditions%20in%20the%20search%20region%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20difficult.%20Weather%20on%20the%20surface%20will%20likely%20provide%20challenges%20for%20the%20support%20vessel%20and%20the%20crew.%20Underwater%20vehicles%20will%20have%20to%20contend%20with%20complex%20conditions%20on%20the%20seafloor%2C%20including%20steep%20slopes%20and%20rough%20terrain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20up%20to%2018%20months.%20Weather%20conditions%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20favourable%20between%20January%20and%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Ocean%20Infinity%20succeeds%20in%20finding%20the%20wreckage%20of%20MH370%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dwbbe4ZXDXl4%5C%22%3Ethe%20Malaysian%20government%20will%20pay%20it%20US%2470%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20steps%20would%20be%20trying%20to%20retrieve%20the%20plane's%20black%20boxes%2C%20which%20would%20enable%20investigators%20to%20piece%20together%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20final%20moments%20before%20the%20plane%20plunged%20into%20the%20ocean.%20The%20Armada%207806%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20remotely%20operated%20vehicles%20onboard%20equipped%20with%20cameras%20and%20manipulator%20systems%2C%20which%20may%20be%20used%20to%20verify%20the%20wreck%20site%20and%20in%20any%20future%20salvage%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Ocean%20Infinity%20fails%2C%20it%20will%20receive%20no%20payment.%20And%20the%20investigation%20into%20the%20location%20of%20the%20plane%20will%20essentially%20be%20back%20to%20square%20one.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F252732%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(Authors%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fstefan-b-williams-1448728%5C%22%3EStefan%20B.%20Williams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Marine%20Robotics%2C%20Australian%20Centre%20for%20Robotics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-sydney-841%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Sydney%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%