revious%20Israeli%20government%20that%20briefly%20forced%20Netanyahu%20from%20power%20between%20June%202021%20and%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20relations%20with%20Netanyahu%20were%20strained%20even%20before%20the%20unprecedented%20October%20Hamas%20attack%20which%20sparked%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20notably%20over%20proposed%20judicial%20reforms%20that%20had%20split%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelations%20worsened%20after%20the%20March%204%20release%20of%20the%20internal%20Shin%20Bet%20report%20on%20the%20Hamas%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20acknowledged%20the%20agency's%20own%20failure%20in%20preventing%20the%20attack%2C%20but%20also%20said%20%26quot%3Ba%20policy%20of%20quiet%20had%20enabled%20Hamas%20to%20undergo%20massive%20military%20buildup%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBar%20had%20already%20hinted%20that%20he%20would%20resign%20before%20the%20end%20of%20his%20term%2C%20taking%20responsibility%20for%20his%20agency's%20failure%20to%20prevent%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecret%20motives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBar's%20dismissal%20provoked%20the%20anger%20of%20the%20opposition%20and%20led%20to%20demonstrations%20accusing%20Netanyahu%20of%20threatening%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20thousand%20people%20braved%20bad%20weather%20late%20Thursday%20to%20demonstrate%20outside%20Netanyahu's%20private%20residence%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20then%20the%20Israeli%20parliament%2C%20where%20ministers%20were%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20made%20public%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Bar%20said%20Netanyahu's%20arguments%20were%20%26quot%3Bgeneral%2C%20unsubstantiated%20accusations%20that%20seem%20to%20hide%20the%20motivations%20behind%20the%20decision%20to%20terminate%20(his)%20duties%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20wrote%20the%20real%20motives%20were%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20interest%26quot%3B%20and%20intended%20to%20%26quot%3Bprevent%20investigations%20into%20the%20events%20leading%20up%20to%20October%207%20and%20other%20serious%20matters%26quot%3B%20being%20looked%20at%20by%20the%20Shin%20Bet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20referred%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bcomplex%2C%20wide-ranging%20and%20highly%20sensitive%20investigation%26quot%3B%20involving%20people%20close%20to%20Netanyahu%20who%20allegedly%20received%20money%20from%20Qatar%2C%20a%20case%20dubbed%20%26quot%3BQatargate%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBar's%20dismissal%20comes%20after%20the%20Israeli%20army%20launched%20a%20series%20of%20massive%20and%20deadly%20bombardments%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20following%20a%20two-month%20truce%20and%20%26quot%3Btargeted%26quot%3B%20ground%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu%20said%20the%20operations%20were%20intended%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20Hamas%20to%20release%20the%2058%20hostages%20remaining%20in%20the%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20rare%20criticism%20of%20Netanyahu%2C%20Israeli%20President%20Isaac%20Herzog%20said%20Thursday%20that%20he%20was%20worried%20the%20resumption%20of%20strikes%20in%20a%20time%20of%20crisis%20could%20undermine%20%26quot%3Bnational%20resilience%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742521620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F5dlso8v_ronen-bar_625x300_21_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-government-sacks-shin-bet-intelligence-chief-ronen-bar-due-to-lack-of-trust-7972783%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20head%20of%20Shin%20Bet%2C%20Israel's%20domestic%20intelligence%20agency%2C%20was%20sacked%20Friday%2C%20days%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20said%20he%20no%20longer%20trusts%20him%2C%20and%20fallout%20from%20a%20report%20on%20the%20October%207%2C%202023%20Hamas%20attack.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-government-sacks-shin-bet-intelligence-chief-ronen-bar-due-to-lack-of-trust-7972783%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ICC%20Considers%20Mammoth%20Changes%20To%20Points%20System%20For%20WTC%202025-27%20Cycle%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Cricket%20Council%20(ICC)%20is%20likely%20to%20ponder%20over%20a%20new%20bonus%20points%20system%20during%20its%20board%20meeting%20in%20April%20which%20could%20give%20more%20weightage%20to%20bigger%20victories%2C%20especially%20overseas%2C%20during%20the%20next%20World%20Test%20Championship%20cycle.%20The%202025-27%20WTC%20cycle%20will%20begin%20with%20India's%20five-match%20away%20Test%20series%20against%20England%20in%20June.%20As%20per%20the%20prevailing%20rules%2C%20the%20team%20winning%20by%20the%20smallest%20margin%20or%20by%20an%20innings%20gets%2012%20points%2C%20six%20points%20for%20a%20tie%20and%20four%20points%20for%20a%20draw.%20But%20this%20could%20see%20a%20change%20as%20the%20global%20governing%20body%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%20Telegraph%2C%20is%20considering%20awarding%20bonus%20points%20for%20innings%20victories%20or%20for%20a%20win%20above%20a%20certain%20big%20margin%20such%20as%20100%20runs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20issues%20such%20as%20giving%20bonus%20points%20for%20innings%20wins%20etc%20has%20been%20in%20continuous%20discussion%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20WTC%2C%20as%20many%20teams%20felt%20that%20due%20weight%20is%20not%20getting%20for%20wins%20against%20big%20teams%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20source%20close%20to%20the%20development%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20such%20topics%20have%20been%20a%20part%20of%20discussions%2C%20and%20this%20could%20again%20come%20up%20for%20deliberations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20could%20now%20change%20as%20the%20ICC%20might%20bring%20in%20bonus%20points%20for%20landslide%20wins%2C%20and%20extra%20points%20could%20be%20given%20to%20victories%20over%20frontline%20teams%20such%20as%20India%2C%20Australia%20and%20England%2C%20as%20per%20their%20rankings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYeah%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20move%20if%20it%20really%20happens.%20The%20teams%20will%20be%20more%20motivated%20to%20go%20for%20results%2C%20as%20we%20could%20see%20some%20exciting%20games%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20former%20India%20player%20told%20PTI%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ICC%20is%20also%20mulling%20giving%20extra%20points%20for%20wins%20away%20from%20home.%20%E2%80%9CYeah%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20motivating%20factor%20for%2C%20you%20know%2C%20those%20%E2%80%98smaller'%20teams%2C%20Look%2C%20when%20New%20Zealand%20beat%20India%20last%20year%2C%20it%20was%20a%20historic%20win%20for%20them%20as%20not%20many%20teams%20came%20here%20and%20beat%20us.%20But%20they%20did%20not%20got%20any%20extra%20points%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20winning%20away%20from%20home%20in%20itself%20can%20act%20as%20a%20motivating%20factor%2C%20now%20the%20teams%20will%20have%20that%20carrot%20in%20front%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20extra%20points%2C%20if%20it%20really%20happens%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20this%2C%20the%20ICC%20board%20meeting%20might%20also%20consider%20the%20two-tier%20Test%20system%2C%20which%20is%20vocally%20supported%20by%20Cricket%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20needs%20a%20lot%20of%20discussion%20before%20putting%20into%20practice%20as%20some%20teams%20might%20feel%20deprived%20of%20regular%20chances%20to%20play%20against%20strong%20teams%20like%20India%20or%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20it%20is%2C%20series%20between%20India%20and%20New%20Zealand%20or%20Australia%20and%20West%20Indies%20are%20less%20in%20numbers%20compared%20to%20series%20between%20top%20teams%20in%20a%20WTC%20cycle.%20So%2C%20they%20should%20th